OL,3,CDid BBC Breakfast segment cross the
OL,4,Cline regarding product prominence?
OL,6,FSome 20 years ago, the BBC completely
OL,7,Fstopped making the kind of on air
OL,8,Freferences to the magazine which were
OL,9,Fonce commonplace. Things like the
OL,10,Freminders an address or a recipe could
OL,11,Fbe found in RT.
OL,13,FAnd it's more than 30 years since
OL,14,FPresentation stopped running trails to
OL,15,Fadvertise RT. Instead slides were
OL,16,Fused, voiced by the announcer, which
OL,17,Falso reminded us other listings
OL,18,Fmagazines were available.
OL,20,FIn other words, RT now has to be
OL,21,Ftreated by BBC programmes just like
OL,22,Fany other commercial product.
