OL,3,CDid BBC Breakfast segment cross the
OL,4,Cline regarding product prominence?
OL,6,FReferences to brands are, of course,
OL,7,Fallowed when they are editorially
OL,8,Fjustified.
OL,10,FIt is perfectly acceptable to
OL,11,Finterview a journalist from RT about
OL,12,Ftelevision ` just like a journalist
OL,13,Ffrom, say, another magazine, newspaper
OL,14,For entertainment website could also be
OL,15,Ffeatured on other occasions.
OL,17,FBut did the item as actually broadcast
OL,18,Fcross the line?
OL,20,FFirstly, the interviewee wore a top
OL,21,Femblazoned with RT's classic logo used
OL,22,Ffrom the 70s until the early 90s.
